summary: Negotiation ongoing with structured proposals. Both parties show cooperativeness through flexibility on budget and decision rights. Equity remains contentious with opposing valuations of IP versus capital. Clear communication reduces ambiguity. Moderate manipulativeness in framing contributions. Fairness perception mixed due to divergent equity positions.

Negotiation remains unresolved with significant equity gap (62/38 vs 55/45). Both parties present structured arguments but use competitive framing. Business Founder's ultimatum increases manipulativeness. Proposals are clear and detailed, minimizing ambiguity. Moderate cooperation exists through budget flexibility, but fairness perception suffers from entrenched positions.

Negotiation failed with parties entrenched at 65/35 vs 55/45 equity splits. Both used structured arguments but employed manipulative tactics including threats and ultimatums. Clear positions but poor cooperation and perceived unfairness prevented agreement.
